to create new module form cli:
    nest generate module messages || nest g module name

to create new controller from cli:
    nest generate controller messages/messages --flat   
                            folder name/call the class messages    -- flat dont create new file 


to create new service: 
        nest g service name
to get the values of the post request in nest:


POST /messages/5?validate=true 
Host: http://localhost:3000
body {"content":"hi there"}

5 = @Param("id") 

validate=true  = @Query()

host = @Headers()

body: @Body()


----- 

validation:

dto => data transfer object

